00:00:13.702 --> 00:00:15.660 align:middle line:84%
>> The early part of my
career was really based

00:00:15.660 --> 00:00:18.210 align:middle line:84%
on understanding the
conventional science.

00:00:18.210 --> 00:00:20.640 align:middle line:84%
I was teaching medical
students, so I was really

00:00:20.640 --> 00:00:22.440 align:middle line:90%
teaching from a curriculum.

00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:24.750 align:middle line:84%
And while I was teaching
conventional science, which

00:00:24.750 --> 00:00:27.850 align:middle line:84%
was based on what is called
"genetic determinism,"

00:00:27.850 --> 00:00:29.925 align:middle line:84%
the belief that genes
control our lives,

00:00:29.925 --> 00:00:32.460 align:middle line:84%
I was engaged with
cloning stem cells.

00:00:32.460 --> 00:00:33.870 align:middle line:84%
And for me, it's
very interesting

00:00:33.870 --> 00:00:37.320 align:middle line:84%
because I was cloning
them back in 1967.

00:00:37.320 --> 00:00:38.760 align:middle line:84%
And at that time,
there were just

00:00:38.760 --> 00:00:40.530 align:middle line:84%
a handful of us in
the entire world that

00:00:40.530 --> 00:00:41.940 align:middle line:90%
even knew what a stem cell was.

00:00:41.940 --> 00:00:45.420 align:middle line:84%
So I was in the right
place at the right time

00:00:45.420 --> 00:00:47.910 align:middle line:84%
with the right
research to reveal

00:00:47.910 --> 00:00:51.120 align:middle line:84%
that what I was teaching in
medical school was incorrect.

00:00:51.120 --> 00:00:53.910 align:middle line:84%
That I started to understand
from the cell culture

00:00:53.910 --> 00:00:56.850 align:middle line:84%
studies that it was
the environment that

00:00:56.850 --> 00:00:59.580 align:middle line:84%
was controlling the genetics,
rather than the genetics

00:00:59.580 --> 00:01:01.530 align:middle line:90%
controlling itself.

00:01:01.530 --> 00:01:03.750 align:middle line:84%
And this, of course,
led to a schism.

00:01:03.750 --> 00:01:05.850 align:middle line:84%
How can I be teaching
in a classroom

00:01:05.850 --> 00:01:08.820 align:middle line:84%
that genes control life and
then go in the laboratory

00:01:08.820 --> 00:01:11.100 align:middle line:84%
and realize that it
was the environment

00:01:11.100 --> 00:01:14.550 align:middle line:84%
in which the cells were living
that controlled the genetics.

00:01:14.550 --> 00:01:17.020 align:middle line:84%
I ended up actually
leaving the system.

00:01:17.020 --> 00:01:17.820 align:middle line:90%
And I walked out.

00:01:17.820 --> 00:01:20.490 align:middle line:90%
I had tenure and walked out.

00:01:20.490 --> 00:01:22.380 align:middle line:84%
But I also then
had an opportunity

00:01:22.380 --> 00:01:26.880 align:middle line:84%
to go into quantum
physics and you go, why?

00:01:26.880 --> 00:01:29.790 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is very
profoundly important.

00:01:29.790 --> 00:01:33.920 align:middle line:84%
As a biologist, almost
all of my colleagues--

00:01:33.920 --> 00:01:36.660 align:middle line:84%
the conventional physics was
called "Newtonian physics."

00:01:36.660 --> 00:01:38.670 align:middle line:84%
Newtonian physics
separates the universe

00:01:38.670 --> 00:01:40.440 align:middle line:84%
into an invisible
energy realm and

00:01:40.440 --> 00:01:42.270 align:middle line:90%
a physical mechanical realm.

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:45.030 align:middle line:84%
Newtonian physics says that
the mechanical realm is not

00:01:45.030 --> 00:01:46.560 align:middle line:90%
affected by the energy realm.

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:49.103 align:middle line:84%
So you want to understand
a physical body,

00:01:49.103 --> 00:01:50.520 align:middle line:84%
then you have to
really understand

00:01:50.520 --> 00:01:52.830 align:middle line:84%
the physical
mechanics of the body

00:01:52.830 --> 00:01:56.160 align:middle line:84%
and ignore the so-called
invisible realm.

00:01:56.160 --> 00:01:58.680 align:middle line:84%
When quantum physics
came in, it completely

00:01:58.680 --> 00:02:00.060 align:middle line:90%
turned the tables on that.

00:02:00.060 --> 00:02:01.050 align:middle line:90%
And it said that--

00:02:01.050 --> 00:02:03.450 align:middle line:84%
it didn't get it didn't get
rid of Newtonian physics.

00:02:03.450 --> 00:02:08.280 align:middle line:84%
Newtonian physics is a smaller
science inside a larger science

00:02:08.280 --> 00:02:09.780 align:middle line:90%
called quantum physics.

00:02:09.780 --> 00:02:12.870 align:middle line:84%
And basically, quantum physics
revealed that everything

00:02:12.870 --> 00:02:14.730 align:middle line:90%
is connected by energy.

00:02:14.730 --> 00:02:17.640 align:middle line:84%
And you say, so why is
this relevant to biology?

00:02:17.640 --> 00:02:21.570 align:middle line:84%
And the answer is,
physics means mechanisms.

00:02:21.570 --> 00:02:26.070 align:middle line:84%
So I can say, quantum
mechanics, quantum physics.

00:02:26.070 --> 00:02:28.500 align:middle line:90%
And I say, physics mechanics.

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:31.530 align:middle line:84%
Mechanics means how things
work in the universe.

00:02:31.530 --> 00:02:33.990 align:middle line:84%
So even if you want
to be a biologist,

00:02:33.990 --> 00:02:36.900 align:middle line:84%
you really have to understand
the mechanics of physics.

00:02:36.900 --> 00:02:40.800 align:middle line:84%
So when quantum physics
came in, it completely

00:02:40.800 --> 00:02:44.910 align:middle line:84%
conflicted with
Newtonian-based medicine.

00:02:44.910 --> 00:02:47.100 align:middle line:84%
And all my colleagues
were Newtonian-based,

00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:48.540 align:middle line:84%
and all of a
sudden, I'd jump off

00:02:48.540 --> 00:02:51.630 align:middle line:84%
into the deep end of
energy medicine, which

00:02:51.630 --> 00:02:53.250 align:middle line:90%
is the new physics.

00:02:53.250 --> 00:02:56.430 align:middle line:84%
And understanding that
led me to a position

00:02:56.430 --> 00:02:58.880 align:middle line:84%
at Stanford University
School of Medicine,

00:02:58.880 --> 00:03:01.110 align:middle line:84%
where I expanded on my
research with cloning

00:03:01.110 --> 00:03:03.840 align:middle line:84%
stem cells and also
about the field--

00:03:03.840 --> 00:03:06.210 align:middle line:84%
the energy field--
and the influence.

00:03:06.210 --> 00:03:09.450 align:middle line:84%
So ultimately, it
led to my finding

00:03:09.450 --> 00:03:11.400 align:middle line:90%
a whole new career for myself.

00:03:11.400 --> 00:03:13.650 align:middle line:84%
And that science--
which is kind of fun,

00:03:13.650 --> 00:03:16.440 align:middle line:84%
